      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark suite with documented order-of-accuracy confirmation at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification documented against ASME V&V 20 benchmarks; second-order spatial accuracy confirmed via Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity tests. Published verification reports available in solver documentation package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating GCI < 5% on primary QoI (RHI) across at least three systematically refined mesh levels at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A two-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 4.2M cells; medium: 8.7M cells). Grid Convergence Index on relative hemolysis index was estimated at 7.3%, marginally exceeding the 5% threshold. The assessment team judged the convergence trend monotonic and the residual error clinically acceptable given the conservative RH < 1 acceptance criterion, and the decision was recorded as Accepted without escalation. A third, fine-mesh level (projected ~18M cells) was scoped for future work but not completed prior to submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented with traceability to device operating envelope; boundary conditions matched within stated uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Bench-top flow loop operated at 37°C with porcine blood (hematocrit 35±2%). Flow rates and rotational speeds replicated the 5 COU operating points within ±1.5% of target values. Pressure boundary conditions derived from clinical CPB flow requirements per AAMI TIR17."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RHI values compared against experimental measurements with agreement within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RHI values at all 5 flow-speed combinations fell within ±12% of experimental measurements. Combined expanded uncertainty (k=2) estimated at 14.8%. All predictions satisfied the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Worst-case operating point (4 L/min, 3500 RPM) showed RHI = 0.87 predicted vs. 0.91 measured."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (RHI, shear stress distribution, exposure time) directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoints relevant to CPB device labeling.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RHI) per ASTM F1841 methodology. Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar stress and Lagrangian particle exposure time. These quantities are directly cited in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device hemolysis assessment and map to the intended regulatory submission endpoint."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities conducted on the same device geometry and fluid under conditions spanning the COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry identical to the COU device. Fluid properties, rotational speed range (2500–4500 RPM), and flow rates (3–6 L/min) fully encompass the 5 COU operating points. No geometric simplifications introduced between validation and COU models."
    },
    {
